value.0: This dwarven armsman looks uncomfortable in his heavy armor, as if he rarely has cause to wear it.
Fashioned from thrice-forged steel, dwarven scale is solid protection from almost any blow.
Resplendent in his Council Robes, this dwarf carries himself with an air of fierce and haughty pride.
There are various ranks and orders within the Brogan's Arm Guild Council, with each having their own garb and insignia. This fine garment probably indicates someone of fairly high rank.
This grizzled veteran of the Guild Council appears to be in a foul mood.

A threadbare road, muddy and rutted, leads south from Brogan's Arm. The gate is locked, however, and under guard.
Rust pocks the once-smooth surface of this metal-plated door.
Fashioned from rough-hewn wood, this simple door swings on ill-fitting hinges.
